#. <section class="sutta" id="mn29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn29:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 29"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 29"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn29:0.2"
msgid "Mahāsāropamasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Simile of the Heartwood"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.192"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn29:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn29:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante "
"devadatte."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left."

msgctxt "mn29:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn29:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, take the case of a person of a good family who has gone forth "
"from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:"

msgctxt "mn29:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi "
"upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto, "
msgstr ""
"‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, "
"sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering. "

msgctxt "mn29:2.3"
msgid ""
"appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti."
msgstr "Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn29:2.4"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity."

msgctxt "mn29:2.5"
msgid "So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr "They’re happy with that, and they’ve got all they wished for."

msgctxt "mn29:2.6"
msgid "So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attānukkaṃseti paraṃ vambheti:"
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down because of that:"

msgctxt "mn29:2.7"
msgid ""
"‘ahamasmi lābhasakkārasilokavā, ime panaññe bhikkhū appaññātā appesakkhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’m the one with possessions, honor, and popularity. These other mendicants "
"are obscure and insignificant.’"

# The instrumental should really be “because of”, see BB’s translation of the similar idiom at AN 8.61. But as the text makes clear, the cause is not really the labha, etc., but the ayoniso manasikara that follows it. This becomes more evident in the following sections dealing with sila, etc. This, i think, justifies the oblique rendering here.
msgctxt "mn29:2.8"
msgid ""
"So tena lābhasakkārasilokena majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto "
"samāno dukkhaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding those "
"possessions, honor, and popularity. And being negligent they live in "
"suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.193"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn29:2.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno "
"mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ "
"atikkamma tacaṃ atikkamma papaṭikaṃ, sākhāpalāsaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya "
"‘sāran’ti maññamāno."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in "
"search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. "
"But, passing over the heartwood, softwood, bark, and shoots, he’d cut off "
"the branches and leaves and depart imagining they were heartwood."

msgctxt "mn29:2.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn29:2.11"
msgid ""
"‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, "
"na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘This gentleman doesn’t know what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or "
"branches and leaves are."

#. VAR: Tathā hayaṃ → tathāpāyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn29:2.12"
msgid ""
"Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno "
"mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ "
"atikkamma tacaṃ atikkamma papaṭikaṃ, sākhāpalāsaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto "
"“sāran”ti maññamāno."
msgstr ""
"That’s why he passed them over, cut off the branches and leaves, and "
"departed imagining they were heartwood."

msgctxt "mn29:2.13"
msgid "Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he won’t succeed.’ …"

msgctxt "mn29:2.14"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajito hoti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:2.15"
msgid ""
"‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi "
"upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto, "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:2.16"
msgid ""
"appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:2.17"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:2.18"
msgid "So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:2.19"
msgid ""
"So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti ‘ahamasmi "
"lābhasakkārasilokavā, ime panaññe bhikkhū appaññātā appesakkhā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:2.20"
msgid ""
"So tena lābhasakkārasilokena majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto "
"samāno dukkhaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:2.21"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sākhāpalāsaṃ aggahesi brahmacariyassa;"
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who has grabbed the branches and leaves of the "
"spiritual life"

msgctxt "mn29:2.22"
msgid "tena ca vosānaṃ āpādi."
msgstr "and stopped short with that."

