msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:10.8"
msgid "Appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:10.9"
msgid "So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:10.10"
msgid "So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:10.11"
msgid ""
"So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto "
"samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:10.12"
msgid "So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:10.13"
msgid "So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn29:10.14"
msgid ""
"So tāya samādhisampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati "
"appamatto samāno ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti."
msgstr "Being diligent, they achieve knowledge and vision."

msgctxt "mn29:10.15"
msgid "So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr "They’re happy with that, and they’ve got all they wished for."

msgctxt "mn29:10.16"
msgid "So tena ñāṇadassanena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:"
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that:"

msgctxt "mn29:10.17"
msgid "‘ahamasmi jānaṃ passaṃ viharāmi."
msgstr "‘I’m the one who meditates knowing and seeing."

msgctxt "mn29:10.18"
msgid "Ime panaññe bhikkhū ajānaṃ apassaṃ viharantī’ti."
msgstr "These other mendicants meditate without knowing and seeing.’"

msgctxt "mn29:10.19"
msgid ""
"So tena ñāṇadassanena majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno "
"dukkhaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that "
"knowledge and vision. And being negligent they live in suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn29:11.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno "
"mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ phegguṃ chetvā ādāya "
"pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in "
"search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. "
"But, passing over the heartwood, he’d cut out the softwood and depart "
"imagining it was heartwood."

msgctxt "mn29:11.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn29:11.3"
msgid ""
"‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ na aññāsi phegguṃ na aññāsi tacaṃ na "
"aññāsi papaṭikaṃ na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘This gentleman doesn’t know what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or "
"branches and leaves are."

msgctxt "mn29:11.4"
msgid ""
"Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno "
"mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ phegguṃ chetvā ādāya "
"pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno."
msgstr ""
"That’s why he passed them over, cut out the softwood, and departed imagining "
"it was heartwood."

msgctxt "mn29:11.5"
msgid "Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he won’t succeed.’ …"

