#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn29:13.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito "
"hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Next, take a person of good family who has gone forth from the lay life to "
"homelessness, thinking:"

msgctxt "mn29:13.2"
msgid ""
"‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi "
"upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto, "
msgstr ""
"‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, "
"sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering. "

msgctxt "mn29:13.3"
msgid ""
"appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti."
msgstr "Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn29:13.4"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti."
msgstr ""
"When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity."

msgctxt "mn29:13.5"
msgid "So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti, na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr "They’re not happy with that, and haven’t got all they wished for."

msgctxt "mn29:13.6"
msgid "So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr "They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "mn29:13.7"
msgid ""
"So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, "
"appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti."
msgstr ""
"Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding those "
"possessions, honor, and popularity. Being diligent, they become accomplished "
"in ethics."

msgctxt "mn29:13.8"
msgid "So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr "They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for."

msgctxt "mn29:13.9"
msgid "So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr "They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "mn29:13.10"
msgid ""
"So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto "
"samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti."
msgstr ""
"Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that "
"accomplishment in ethics. Being diligent, they achieve immersion."

msgctxt "mn29:13.11"
msgid "So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr "They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for."

msgctxt "mn29:13.12"
msgid "So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr "They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "mn29:13.13"
msgid ""
"So tāya samādhisampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, "
"appamatto samāno ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti."
msgstr ""
"Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that "
"accomplishment in immersion. Being diligent, they achieve knowledge and "
"vision."

msgctxt "mn29:13.14"
msgid "So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr "They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for."

msgctxt "mn29:13.15"
msgid "So tena ñāṇadassanena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr "They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "mn29:13.16"
msgid ""
"So tena ñāṇadassanena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto "
"samāno asamayavimokkhaṃ ārādheti."
msgstr ""
"Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that "
"knowledge and vision. Being diligent, they achieve permanent liberation."

#. VAR: anavakāso → vijjati (s1-3)
#. VAR: Aṭṭhānametaṃ → ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ (s1-3, pts1) | aṭṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn29:13.17"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu tāya asamayavimuttiyā "
"parihāyetha."
msgstr ""
"And it’s impossible for that mendicant to fall away from that permanent "
"liberation."

#. </p><p>
